phase2.explanation:
`Input` methods only work in `Update()` — they're frame-based.

**The fix:**
```csharp
void Update()
{
    if (Input.GetButtonDown("Jump"))
    {
        Debug.Log("Jumped!");
    }
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Input is frame-based. Always use it in `Update()`, not `Start()`."
